## PRIORITY 4 — Frame Grid: Focus Mode (Expandable Full Screen)

Add an expand icon (⛶) at the top-right of the Frame Grid panel. 
Clicking it opens Focus Mode — a full-screen overlay covering the 
entire page (z-index above all panels).

### Focus Mode layout
Left 65%: enlarged frame grid. Right 35%: live page table.

### Enlarged frame cards
Each card is now significantly larger and shows:
- Frame ID (top-left, monospace, small)
- Process name (center, bold, large)
- Page number (below process name, muted)
- Load timestamp (bottom-left, tiny, muted): "Loaded 4s ago"
- Last accessed (bottom-right, tiny): "Used 1s ago"
- For LRU: a thin horizontal "age bar" at the bottom of the card 
  that fills left-to-right as time passes since last access. When 
  this bar is nearly full, the card gets a subtle amber outline 
  indicating it's the LRU candidate.
- FREE state: dashed border, grey background, centered "EMPTY" text

### Page load animation in Focus Mode
When a new page loads into a frame, animate it sliding in from the 
bottom of the screen with a smooth arc into its target frame card. 
Duration: 400ms, easing: ease-out.

When a frame is evicted, the card content dissolves out (opacity 0, 
slight scale-down) over 300ms before the new content slides in.

When a hit occurs (no eviction), the frame card briefly glows with 
a green ring (box-shadow pulse, 300ms).

### Live page table (right side of Focus Mode)
A two-column table: "Page" and "Frame". One row per allocated page 
across all active processes. Group rows by process with a colored 
left border per process. Updates live as mappings change. Rows 
animate in/out as pages are loaded/evicted.

### Close Focus Mode
Clicking the ✕ button or pressing Escape closes Focus Mode with a 
smooth shrink animation back to the normal panel layout.

