## PRIORITY 7 — Learning Mode: Full Rewrite

The existing scenario annotation system fires at wrong moments and 
shows irrelevant text. Replace it entirely with a step-by-step 
narrated walkthrough system.

### Structural changes
When a scenario starts:
- The right 30% of the screen slides in a "Narrator Panel" (a 
  dedicated sidebar, not an overlay). It sits beside the Frame Grid.
- The Frame Grid shrinks from 60% to 42% width to accommodate.
- The Narrator Panel has: scenario title, step progress indicator 
  (e.g. "Step 2 of 5"), a heading, 2–4 sentences of explanation, 
  and a "Next Step →" button at the bottom.
- A speed toggle at the top: "Manual" (waits for Next Step click) 
  and "Auto" (advances on its own after each step completes).

### Visual highlighting from narrator
Each step in the scenario JSON can specify UI elements to highlight. 
The frontend should support:
- highlight_frame: [3] → frame card 3 pulses with a glow ring
- highlight_ref_index: [4] → pill at index 4 in reference string 
  pulses
- highlight_stat: "fault_count" → fault counter in stats bar pulses
- highlight_log: true → log panel gets a bright border

When a step is active, highlighted elements have a slow pulsing 
glow (CSS keyframe animation) until the step advances.

